## Scope

This packet compiles one project programming fact sheet per candidate project
in ClawModeler run `{{ run_id }}`. It is intended to be handed to a Caltrans
District Local Assistance Engineer (DLAE) or incorporated into the lead
agency's *Local Assistance Procedures Manual* (LAPM) Chapter 3 (Project
Authorization) and Chapter 7 (Field Review) submittal.

## Methodology

Each fact sheet below pairs ClawModeler's four-dimension screening scores
(safety, equity, climate, feasibility — each 0–100, weighted 30/25/25/20 into
the total) with the LAPM-style programming fields that a lead agency must
populate. Fields that the lead agency has not yet supplied are labeled
explicitly; ClawModeler does **not** invent scope, cost, schedule, or
environmental information it does not have evidence for.

